WEBVTT

00:02.203 --> 00:04.035
(Vince Guaraldi's "Christmas
Time Is Here" playing)

00:04.035 --> 00:06.037
(Meredith) THE BEST GIFT
I EVER GOT

00:06.037 --> 00:08.339
WAS FOR CHRISTMAS
WHEN I WAS 10...

00:08.339 --> 00:10.511
MY VERY FIRST SUTURE KIT.

00:10.511 --> 00:13.084
I USED IT
UNTIL MY FINGERS BLED,

00:13.084 --> 00:16.447
AND THEN I TRIED TO USE IT
TO STITCH UP MY FINGERS.

00:16.447 --> 00:18.449
THANK YOU FOR MEETING ME.

00:18.449 --> 00:22.022
YOU'RE THE CHIEF OF SURGERY.
IF YOU PAGE, I'M HERE.

00:22.022 --> 00:26.026
IT PUT ME ON THE PATH
TO BECOMING A SURGEON.

00:26.026 --> 00:29.360
♪ SNOWFLAKES IN THE AIR ♪

00:29.360 --> 00:31.762
I WANT TO SAY SOMETHING.

00:31.762 --> 00:34.165
I NEED TO SAY SOMETHING...

00:34.165 --> 00:37.168
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED
THE OTHER NIGHT.

00:37.168 --> 00:40.371
I-I NEED YOU TO KNOW
IT WASN'T...

00:40.371 --> 00:44.815
WELL, IT ISN'T
WHAT YOU THINK.

00:44.815 --> 00:48.048
OH. I DON'T THINK ANYTHING

00:48.048 --> 00:50.050
ABOUT YOUR
PERSONAL LIFE, SIR.

00:50.050 --> 00:52.183
♪ BEAUTY EVERYWHERE ♪

00:52.183 --> 00:54.425
♪ YULETIDE BY... ♪

00:54.425 --> 00:57.828
I HAD A PROBLEM...
A LONG TIME AGO.

00:57.828 --> 01:01.192
I WAS DIAGNOSED
WITH ALCOHOLISM.

01:01.192 --> 01:03.534
OR I DIAGNOSED MYSELF.

01:03.534 --> 01:07.568
AND I DIDN'T TAKE A DRINK
FOR ALMOST 20 YEARS.

01:07.568 --> 01:09.570
BUT I THINK
IT WAS A MISDIAGNOSIS.

01:09.570 --> 01:13.244
I'M NOT SAYING MY DRINKING
WASN'T BAD, BECAUSE IT WAS.

01:13.244 --> 01:16.207
BUT THERE IS
SUCH A THING AS...

01:16.207 --> 01:18.709
SITUATIONAL DEPRESSION.

01:18.709 --> 01:21.212
AND I THINK THAT'S WHAT
I WAS SUFFERING FROM,

01:21.212 --> 01:24.615
AND IT ESCALATED MY DRINKING.

01:24.615 --> 01:27.218
SITUATIONAL DEPRESSION?

01:27.218 --> 01:29.220
YOUR MOTHER.
(laugh) YES.

01:29.220 --> 01:31.822
(chuckles)
WELL, SHE ESCALATED
MY DRINKING, TOO, SO...

01:31.822 --> 01:33.524
(laughs)

01:33.524 --> 01:36.267
♪♪

01:36.267 --> 01:38.269
HAVE YOU TOLD ANYONE
WHAT YOU SAW?

01:38.269 --> 01:40.801
I MEAN, HAVE YOU TOLD DEREK?

01:40.801 --> 01:42.573
NO.

01:42.573 --> 01:43.704
MM-HMM.

01:43.704 --> 01:45.105
NO.

01:45.105 --> 01:47.208
♪♪

01:47.208 --> 01:50.611
WELL... SINCE I TOOK
A STEP BACK FROM SURGERY,

01:50.611 --> 01:55.586
I'VE HAD SOME TIME TO REALLY
LOOK AT OUR RESIDENTS.

01:55.586 --> 01:57.888
AND YOUR WORK...

01:57.888 --> 02:01.352
YOUR RAW TALENT...

02:01.352 --> 02:03.554
(sighs)

02:03.554 --> 02:05.856
IS EXTRAORDINARY.

02:05.856 --> 02:09.700
A LOT LIKE YOUR MOTHER'S.

02:09.700 --> 02:12.233
AND SINCE I HAVE SOME TIME--

02:12.233 --> 02:14.235
SOME EXTRA TIME--

02:14.235 --> 02:15.536
UM...

02:15.536 --> 02:17.868
♪ SUCH SPIRIT
THROUGH THE YEAR ♪

02:17.868 --> 02:21.712
MAYBE YOU WOULD LIKE
A MENTOR.

02:21.712 --> 02:25.316
MAYBE I COULD TEACH YOU
SOME THINGS.

02:25.316 --> 02:29.650
HAVE YOU EVER DONE
A 2-LAYERED, CONTINUOUS SUTURE

02:29.650 --> 02:31.652
FOR AN ANASTOMOSIS?

02:31.652 --> 02:33.654
MY POINT IS,
SOMETIMES THE BEST GIFTS

02:33.654 --> 02:36.327
COME IN
REALLY SURPRISING PACKAGES.

02:36.327 --> 02:38.158
NO.

02:38.158 --> 02:40.331
TAKE A SEAT.

02:40.331 --> 02:43.334
♪♪

02:45.366 --> 02:47.538
YOU'RE ABOUT TO.

02:50.401 --> 02:51.902
♪♪

02:51.902 --> 02:54.305
(pager beeping and buzzing)

02:54.305 --> 02:56.807
♪ SLEIGH BELLS IN THE AIR ♪

02:56.807 --> 02:58.309
(laughs) WAIT.

02:58.309 --> 02:59.310
(laughs)

02:59.310 --> 03:00.711
(chuckles)

03:00.711 --> 03:03.714
OH, IT'S TEDDY.
AH, I LOVE IT WHEN IT'S TEDDY.

03:03.714 --> 03:04.885
OKAY.

03:04.885 --> 03:07.558
♪ YULETIDE BY THE FIRESIDE ♪

03:07.558 --> 03:09.260
♪ AND JOYFUL MEMORIES... ♪

03:09.260 --> 03:12.223
DON'T YOU THINK IT'S STRANGE
THAT HE'S MENTORING YOU AT NIGHT

03:12.223 --> 03:14.365
AND STILL NOT TALKING TO ME?

03:14.365 --> 03:17.898
SINCE THE MERGER, IT IS
IMPOSSIBLE TO GET O.R. TIME.
AND WHO IS RESPONSIBLE
FOR THAT?

03:17.898 --> 03:21.402
THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING.
I NEED ALL THE HELP I CAN GET.

03:21.402 --> 03:24.405
AND I AM SAYING,
HE IS USING YOU TO GET TO ME.
HE IS NOT.

03:24.405 --> 03:27.908
THEN WHY NOW? WHY ARE YOU
SUDDENLY SEEING SO MUCH OF HIM?
I'M DONE TALKING ABOUT THIS.

03:27.908 --> 03:29.910
IF YOU WANT TO STAY MAD,
STAY MAD.

03:29.910 --> 03:31.912
BUT I'M JUST GONNA BE HERE
KISSING YOU.

03:31.912 --> 03:34.315
(laughs)

03:36.587 --> 03:39.290
(Cristina) OH, MY GOD.
(Jackson) OH, MY GOD. WOW.

03:39.290 --> 03:41.922
THAT IS THE BIGGEST
PSEUDOANEURYSM I'VE EVER SEEN.
IT'S AT THE SUTURE LINE
OF THE TRANSPLANT.

03:41.922 --> 03:44.895
THE NEW HEART IS DYING.
DAMN IT.
POOR GUY THAT BROUGHT HER IN.

03:44.895 --> 03:46.957
I THINK THEY WERE ON
THEIR THIRD DATE.

03:46.957 --> 03:49.960
IT DOESN'T EVEN LOOK
LIKE A HEART ANYMORE.
THAT'S BECAUSE IT'S NOT.

03:49.960 --> 03:53.964
IT'S A CHUNK OF USELESS FLESH
THAT HAS TO COME OUT RIGHT NOW.
YOU'RE TAKING THE HEART OUT?

03:53.964 --> 03:56.407
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA
REPLACE IT WITH?

03:56.407 --> 04:04.945
I DON'T KNOW. WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO FIGURE IT OUT AS WE GO.

04:04.945 --> 04:06.947
OKAY, WAIT.
LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.

04:06.947 --> 04:09.019
YOU REMOVED HER HEART?
YES.

04:09.019 --> 04:11.021
A-AND SHE CAN LIVE
THAT WAY?

04:11.021 --> 04:13.954
LIKE--LIKE WHAT,
LIKE A-A VAMPIRE?
USUALLY YOU'D CONNECT

04:13.954 --> 04:16.627
A VENTRICULAR ASSIST DEVICE
TO THE HEART,

04:16.627 --> 04:18.629
BUT SINCE SHE DOESN'T
HAVE A HEART--

04:18.629 --> 04:21.562
DR. ALTMAN ATTACHED TWO, UM,
DEVICES TO HER BLOOD VESSELS.

04:21.562 --> 04:24.535
NOW THIS MACHINE NOW PUMPS
THE BLOOD THROUGH HER BODY,

04:24.535 --> 04:27.298
WHICH IS BASICALLY, UM,
A MIRACLE.

04:27.298 --> 04:29.340
I REALLY LIKE HER.
UH, I LIKE HER A LOT.

04:29.340 --> 04:31.041
BUT WE'VE ONLY HAD FOUR DATES.

04:31.041 --> 04:32.943
I'M SUPPOSED
TO HAVE THANKSGIVING

04:32.943 --> 04:34.645
WITH MY FAMILY, YOU KNOW?

04:34.645 --> 04:36.707
SHE WAS GONNA JOIN US.

04:36.707 --> 04:38.008
AND NOW SHE'S LIKE A...

04:38.008 --> 04:41.281
SHE CAN REALLY LIVE
WITHOUT A HEART?

04:41.281 --> 04:42.983
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO STAY,
WE HAVE A GREAT NURSING STAFF,

04:42.983 --> 04:44.715
GREAT DOCTORS.

04:44.715 --> 04:46.317
SHE'LL BE IN GOOD HANDS.

04:46.317 --> 04:49.320
NO. YOU KNOW, SHE DOESN'T
EVEN HAVE A FAMILY.

04:49.320 --> 04:52.323
AND IF IT WAS ME,
I WOULD WANT SOMEBODY HERE.

04:52.323 --> 04:53.924
SO... I'LL STAY.

04:56.997 --> 04:58.298
OKAY.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.773
TUCKER AND LITTLE TUCK
ARE BOTH FINE.

05:02.773 --> 05:04.375
YEAH, I KNOW.

05:04.375 --> 05:08.539
I'M SORRY I HAVE TO WORK TODAY
AND ON CHRISTMAS THIS YEAR.

05:08.539 --> 05:12.443
YEAH. UH, TUCKER AND I
WERE HOPING TO BRING HIM HOME

05:12.443 --> 05:14.314
TO VISIT YOU.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.547
MOM, UM, I HAVE TO GO.

05:16.547 --> 05:19.590
HAPPY THANKSGIVING, MOM.

05:19.590 --> 05:22.623
YOU DIDN'T TELL YOUR PARENTS
ABOUT THE DIVORCE?
(clicking keyboard keys)

05:22.623 --> 05:25.325
HOW LONG CAN YOU
KEEP THAT A SECRET?

05:25.325 --> 05:26.827
WHEN YOU STARTED
DATING WOMEN,

05:26.827 --> 05:29.960
HOW LONG DID YOU KEEP
THAT SECRET FROM YOUR FAMILY?

05:29.960 --> 05:31.101
(elevator bell dings)

05:31.101 --> 05:33.333
OKAY.
WH--

05:33.333 --> 05:36.507
WHEN DID THE BLEEDING START?
THIS MORNING.
HE'S HAD THESE BEFORE.

05:36.507 --> 05:39.640
I JUST... I'VE NEVER SEEN
A NOSEBLEED GO ON LIKE THIS.

05:39.640 --> 05:42.072
THERE'S BLOOD ON TIMMY, MOM.

05:42.072 --> 05:44.815
MR. AND MRS. JACOBSEN,
CAN I SEE YOU?

05:44.815 --> 05:47.077
GO AHEAD.
WE'LL BE FINE.

05:47.077 --> 05:50.020
NICHOLAS HAS WHAT IS CALLED
AN ARTERIOVENOUS MALFORMATION.

05:50.020 --> 05:52.653
IT'S A CLUSTER OF TANGLED
BLOOD VESSELS IN HIS BRAIN.

05:52.653 --> 05:56.126
IT'S WHAT'S CAUSING
THE BLEEDING.
IN ORDER TO STOP THE BLEEDING,
WE NEED TO REMOVE IT.

05:56.126 --> 05:58.559
Y-Y-YOU MEAN LIKE
BRAIN SURGERY OR...
(exhales)

05:58.559 --> 06:01.061
I'LL DO EVERYTHING I CAN
TO PROTECT THE BRAIN TISSUE

06:01.061 --> 06:04.064
AND MINIMIZE DAMAGE.
I'M SORRY.
I KNOW IT'S SCARY.

06:04.064 --> 06:07.568
BUT WE HAVE TO GO IN
RIGHT AWAY.

06:15.646 --> 06:17.648
EXCUSE ME.
(man screaming)

06:17.648 --> 06:19.950
I'M LOOKING
FOR DR. MARK SLOAN.

06:19.950 --> 06:22.913
UM, YOU SEE THE DUDE
WHO WAS BURNED...
(screams and whimpers)

06:22.913 --> 06:25.055
TRYING TO DEEP FRY A TURKEY?

06:25.055 --> 06:28.058
SLOAN'S THE GUY
MAKING HIM SCREAM LIKE A GIRL.
NO!

06:28.058 --> 06:29.990
(grunts and screams)

06:29.990 --> 06:31.492
(man) OH.

06:31.492 --> 06:33.023
DR. SLOAN?

06:33.023 --> 06:34.495
YEAH.
(grunting and groaning)

06:34.495 --> 06:36.667
HI.

06:36.667 --> 06:38.999
UM, SO THIS IS
A LITTLE WEIRD,

06:38.999 --> 06:42.072
BUT, UM... MY NAME
IS SLOAN REILLY.

06:42.072 --> 06:44.905
AND, UH, MY MOM'S
SAMANTHA REILLY.

06:44.905 --> 06:47.638
AND, UM... I'M PRETTY SURE
YOU'RE MY DAD.

07:15.105 --> 07:16.767
HI.

07:16.767 --> 07:19.039
HOW'S IT, UH,
HOW'S IT GOING IN HERE?

07:19.039 --> 07:20.741
GREAT.
FINE.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.212
OKAY.

07:22.212 --> 07:26.947
SO HAVE WE BROACHED THE QUESTION
OF A PATERNITY TEST?

07:26.947 --> 07:29.920
'CAUSE I BROUGHT SUPPLIES.

07:29.920 --> 07:32.923
(Lexie) SHE'S 18. THAT'S NOT
VERY MUCH YOUNGER THAN ME.

07:32.923 --> 07:35.055
WELL, IT'S NOT
THAT SHOCKING ACTUALLY.

07:35.055 --> 07:38.028
I MEAN, THE WAY MARK GOT AROUND
BEFORE HE MET YOU,

07:38.028 --> 07:40.861
THERE COULD BE
A GAGGLE OF SLOANS.

07:40.861 --> 07:45.165
SLOAN JONES. SLOAN SMITH.
SLOAN SLOAN. (laughs)
MEAN.

07:45.165 --> 07:47.938
AH, DAMN IT.

07:47.938 --> 07:50.771
SON OF A BITCH.

07:50.771 --> 07:53.604
I CAN'T ACCESS THE FEEDERS.

07:53.604 --> 07:56.907
SO... WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
IT MEANS
I CAN'T GET AT IT.

07:56.907 --> 07:58.909
I CAN DO A TEMPORARY FIX,

07:58.909 --> 08:01.882
BUT ONCE HE STARTS BLEEDING
AGAIN, WHICH HE WILL,

08:01.882 --> 08:03.954
THERE WON'T BE ANYTHING
WE CAN DO.

08:03.954 --> 08:08.088
SO WE'RE JUST GONNA...
SEND HIM HOME TO DIE?

08:08.088 --> 08:10.991
HAPPY THANKSGIVING,
JACOBSEN FAMILY.

08:10.991 --> 08:12.022
(sighs)

08:20.731 --> 08:22.172
NICE DAY.

08:22.172 --> 08:24.104
LITTLE CHILLY.
HMM. YEAH.

08:28.639 --> 08:30.611
IT'S BRISK, THOUGH.
IT'S NOT COLD.

08:30.611 --> 08:31.912
RIGHT.

08:37.788 --> 08:40.250
(siren wailing)

08:40.250 --> 08:43.193
LOOK, TEDDY...

08:43.193 --> 08:46.156
NO. I... I KNOW.

08:46.156 --> 08:49.029
(wailing continues)

08:49.029 --> 08:51.832
I-I-I-I DON'T--
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

08:51.832 --> 08:54.805
YOU--YOU SAID THAT--THAT HE
WOULD DIE WITHOUT THE SURGERY.

08:54.805 --> 08:58.168
AND NOW YOU'RE TELLING US WE'RE
SUPPOSED TO JUST TAKE HIM HOME?

08:58.168 --> 09:00.040
RIGHT. WELL, I'VE STOPPED
THE BLEEDING TEMPORARILY.

09:00.040 --> 09:02.973
BUT THE ONLY WAY TO REMOVE
THE A.V.M. SAFELY

09:02.973 --> 09:04.845
IS THROUGH THE SINUS.
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU DO THAT?

09:04.845 --> 09:07.547
BECAUSE THERE ARE NO INSTRUMENTS
THAT CAN MANEUVER THROUGH

09:07.547 --> 09:11.782
A NASAL CAVITY THIS SMALL
AND GET THE APPROPRIATE ANGLES.
WHY NOT? WHO DOES THAT?

09:11.782 --> 09:13.854
WHO INVENTS THOSE THINGS?

09:17.888 --> 09:19.229
MARK...

09:19.229 --> 09:24.895
NOW MIGHT BE A GOOD PLACE
FOR YOU TO SAY SOMETHING.

09:24.895 --> 09:26.236
OUT LOUD.

09:26.236 --> 09:30.771
DUDE, ARE YOU, LIKE,
HIGH OR SOMETHING?

09:30.771 --> 09:32.643
SLOAN.
YEAH.

09:32.643 --> 09:35.946
YES.
(chuckles) MARK, I NEED YOU
ON SOMETHING.

09:35.946 --> 09:37.948
I HAVE A DAUGHTER, DEREK.
YEAH.

09:37.948 --> 09:39.249
AN 18-YEAR-OLD DAUGHTER.

09:39.249 --> 09:41.952
I AM TOO YOUNG TO HAVE
AN 18 YEAR OLD.

09:41.952 --> 09:45.656
IT'S A NAIL IN MY COFFIN. IT'S
LIKE DEATH HAS COME TO CALL.
OKAY, CAN WE PUT A PIN

09:45.656 --> 09:48.989
IN YOUR EXISTENTIAL CRISIS
FOR A MINUTE?
NO. THAT'S WHY THEY CALL IT
A CRISIS.

09:48.989 --> 09:50.991
LOOK, DR. ROBBINS AND I
HAVE A 6 YEAR OLD

09:50.991 --> 09:52.993
WITH AN INOPERABLE A.V.M.

09:52.993 --> 09:55.225
WE NEED YOUR HELP
TO MAKE IT OPERABLE.
(exhales deeply)

09:55.225 --> 09:59.099
THIS IS
THE BEST THANKSGIVING EVER.

09:59.099 --> 10:00.931
NO OBNOXIOUS RELATIVES.

10:00.931 --> 10:02.773
NO STUPID TRADITIONS.

10:02.773 --> 10:05.035
(scoffs) NO GOING AROUND
THE TABLE AND SAYING

10:05.035 --> 10:08.839
WHAT YOU'RE GRATEFUL FOR.
YEAH, I THINK WE SHOULD DO
THE OPPOSITE.

10:08.839 --> 10:11.842
TALK ABOUT WHAT WE'RE
NOT GRATEFUL FOR.
THE MERGER.

10:11.842 --> 10:15.245
THE MERCY WESTERS.
THEY'RE LIKE THE PLAGUE. I MEAN,
STEALING ALL OUR SURGERIES,

10:15.245 --> 10:17.748
EATING ALL THAT PIE
IN THE NURSES' STATION.

10:17.748 --> 10:20.120
YOU'RE DOING THAT WRONG.
I AM NOT.

10:20.120 --> 10:23.053
YOU ARE. CAN I SHOW YOU?

10:23.053 --> 10:25.125
(scoffs) PRIVATE LESSONS
WITH THE CHIEF...

10:25.125 --> 10:28.358
MAN, THOSE DADDY ISSUES
ARE WORKING FOR YOU.

10:28.358 --> 10:30.761
I DON'T HAVE DADDY ISSUES.
HE'S TEACHING ME.

10:30.761 --> 10:33.063
YOU'RE HIS BITCH.
WELL, IN THAT CASE,
YOU'RE TEDDY'S BITCH.

10:33.063 --> 10:35.405
MAYBE THAT'S MY PROBLEM.
I'M NOBODY'S BITCH.

10:35.405 --> 10:38.809
OH, WELL,
YOU WERE IZZIE'S BITCH.
YOU'RE THE BITCH.

10:38.809 --> 10:40.210
YOU KNOW WHAT?
IT'S THANKSGIVING.
WELL--

10:40.210 --> 10:42.943
CAN WE JUST HAVE
NO NAME-CALLING?
YEAH. PLEASE.

10:42.943 --> 10:45.946
WHATEVER. JUST SHOW ME
THAT STITCH AGAIN.

10:45.946 --> 10:49.079
(crunching)

10:49.079 --> 10:51.952
(knock on door)

10:51.952 --> 10:53.924
(all) HEY!

10:53.924 --> 10:55.956
(Sloan) HEY.

10:55.956 --> 10:57.788
HI.
HELLO.

10:57.788 --> 11:01.862
WELCOME. HAPPY THANKSGIVING.
WHO WANTS WINE?

11:01.862 --> 11:03.894
OOH, I DO.
NO, YOU--YOU DON'T.

11:03.894 --> 11:06.937
UM... HEY, EVERYBODY.

11:06.937 --> 11:09.069
UH, WELL,
THE RESULTS ARE IN.

11:09.069 --> 11:12.873
IT, UH, TURNS OUT
SLOAN WAS RIGHT

11:12.873 --> 11:14.174
ABOUT HER PARENTAGE.

11:14.174 --> 11:16.877
I AM HER DAD.

11:16.877 --> 11:20.310
UM, SO HERE'S ANOTHER THING
TO BE THANKFUL FOR.

11:20.310 --> 11:22.853
LEXIE, SLOAN HERE

11:22.853 --> 11:25.856
IS GONNA MOVE IN WITH US
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

11:25.856 --> 11:27.017
(chops)

11:29.689 --> 11:33.193
OH, MY GOD.
OH!

11:33.193 --> 11:34.865
OUCH.

11:42.402 --> 11:46.837
(folk version of
"Joy to the World" playing)

11:46.837 --> 11:48.839
NOW JUST--JUST EASE UP.

11:48.839 --> 11:50.941
LET THE SUTURE
DO THE WORK FOR YOU.

11:50.941 --> 11:52.943
YOU KNOW, IT'S LIKE A DANCE.

11:52.943 --> 11:55.445
YOU KNOW, YOU LET THE NEEDLE
BE THE MAN,

11:55.445 --> 11:56.947
LET IT TAKE THE LEAD,

11:56.947 --> 11:59.019
AND LET YOUR HAND JUST FOLLOW.

11:59.019 --> 12:03.223
LOOK AT THAT. I HAVEN'T SEEN
SKILL LIKE THAT SINCE...

12:03.223 --> 12:05.926
SINCE YOUR MOTHER.

12:05.926 --> 12:09.099
THAT WOMAN...
SHE COULD DANCE.

12:09.099 --> 12:12.732
YOU SHOULD
MAKE UP WITH DEREK.

12:12.732 --> 12:15.936
IT'S CHRISTMAS. IT'S TIME.

12:15.936 --> 12:17.237
♪♪

12:17.237 --> 12:20.210
YOU NEED TO TAKE
PERPENDICULAR BITES

12:20.210 --> 12:23.143
ABOUT A MILLIMETER APART.

12:23.143 --> 12:26.046
(man) ♪ LET EARTH RECEIVE... ♪

12:26.046 --> 12:27.747
HOW'S IT FEEL?

12:27.747 --> 12:29.449
STILL TINGLING?
OH, IT'S FINE.

12:29.449 --> 12:32.382
I PRETTY MUCH
HAVE FULL SENSATION.

12:32.382 --> 12:33.884
GREAT. GOOD.

12:33.884 --> 12:35.926
SO...

12:35.926 --> 12:37.888
HAVE YOU, UH...

12:37.888 --> 12:40.390
I MEAN, UH, YOU THINK
YOU COULD ASK HER

12:40.390 --> 12:43.994
HOW LONG
SHE'S PLANNING TO STAY?

12:43.994 --> 12:45.996
MARK, IT'S BEEN A MONTH,

12:45.996 --> 12:48.098
AND YOU'VE EXCHANGED
THREE SENTENCES WITH HER.

12:48.098 --> 12:51.041
TWO OF THEM WERE,
"PASS THE CEREAL."

12:51.041 --> 12:52.943
IN THE SPIRIT OF THE HOLIDAY,

12:52.943 --> 12:54.945
MAYBE YOU CAN
ASK HER YOURSELF.

12:54.945 --> 12:58.048
SHE'S PRETTY EASY TO LIKE
ONCE YOU GET TO KNOW HER.
REALLY?

12:58.048 --> 13:00.780
NO. SHE'S A VAPID,
VAPID GIRL,

13:00.780 --> 13:03.954
BUT SHE'S YOUR DAUGHTER, OKAY?
SO--SO TRY.

13:03.954 --> 13:06.917
OKAY?
TRY--TRY TO BE HER DAD.

13:06.917 --> 13:08.788
(exhales deeply)

13:08.788 --> 13:10.991
GO.

13:10.991 --> 13:13.493
UH... (clears throat)

13:13.493 --> 13:17.297
♪♪

13:17.297 --> 13:20.931
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT,
YOU OLD PERV?

13:20.931 --> 13:22.903
(knock on door)

13:22.903 --> 13:24.334
MM.

13:24.334 --> 13:26.076
DAD!

13:26.076 --> 13:27.938
MERRY CHRISTMAS.
(chuckles)

13:27.938 --> 13:29.239
MM.
UH...

13:29.239 --> 13:31.341
UH, YOUR MOTHER SENT ME.

13:31.341 --> 13:33.043
UH-OH. YOU HEARD.

13:33.043 --> 13:34.344
YOUR COUSIN SAID SOMETHING

13:34.344 --> 13:37.147
TO HER HUSBAND
IN FRONT OF YOUR NIECE,

13:37.147 --> 13:39.890
WHO SAID SOMETHING
TO YOUR YOUNGER NIECE,

13:39.890 --> 13:42.252
WHO SAID SOMETHING
TO YOUR MOTHER.
OH.

13:42.252 --> 13:43.994
MM.
UH...

13:43.994 --> 13:47.497
I-I WAS PLANNING TO PUT
A TREE UP, I JUST--
AND WHERE'S TUCK?

13:47.497 --> 13:49.499
HE'S BACK EAST
WITH TUCKER'S FAMILY.

13:49.499 --> 13:52.362
HE WAS WITH ME
FOR THANKSGIVING.
SO IT'S TRUE.

13:52.362 --> 13:54.364
YOU ARE GETTING A DIVORCE.

13:54.364 --> 13:56.066
♪♪

13:56.066 --> 13:58.838
(machine whirring)

13:58.838 --> 14:02.072
IT'S WEIRD.

14:02.072 --> 14:04.544
NO HEARTBEAT.

14:04.544 --> 14:06.546
I USED TO CLIMB MOUNTAINS,
YOU KNOW?

14:06.546 --> 14:09.019
ONE TIME I DID THE INCA TRAIL.

14:09.019 --> 14:11.251
IT'S FOUR MOUNTAINS
IN THREE DAYS.

14:11.251 --> 14:13.253
THE SECOND DAY
THERE'S THIS CLIMB.

14:13.253 --> 14:16.026
IT'S EIGHT HOURS STRAIGHT.

14:16.026 --> 14:17.427
AND YOU ARE SO TIRED,

14:17.427 --> 14:20.991
AND THE AIR IS SO THIN,
YOU DON'T EVEN TALK.

14:20.991 --> 14:22.993
ALL YOU DO IS CLIMB.

14:22.993 --> 14:26.636
AND IT'S JUST YOU
AND YOUR BREATHING

14:26.636 --> 14:30.340
AND YOUR HEARTBEAT
POUNDING IN YOUR EARS.

14:30.340 --> 14:34.304
IT'S JUST HARD
GETTING USED TO NO HEARTBEAT.

14:36.106 --> 14:38.949
AND I'M GETTING TIRED.

14:41.611 --> 14:43.483
REALLY TIRED.

14:43.483 --> 14:45.916
I KNOW.

14:45.916 --> 14:48.959
YOU KNOW WHAT? YOU JUST NEED TO
HANG ON TILL NEW YEAR'S EVE.

14:48.959 --> 14:51.421
THERE'S A LOT OF DRUNK DRIVERS,
A LOT OF BRAIN DEATH.

14:51.421 --> 14:53.493
IT'S AN ORGAN-PALOOZA.
(chuckles)

14:53.493 --> 14:55.625
(clears throat)

14:55.625 --> 14:58.999
KELSEY, YOU JUST
GOTTA HANG ON, OKAY?

14:58.999 --> 15:01.471
YOU'LL HIKE AGAIN,
YOU KNOW?

15:01.471 --> 15:04.034
WE'LL HIKE TOGETHER.

15:04.034 --> 15:07.407
IT'S SUCH A BEAUTIFUL WORLD
OUTSIDE OF THIS HOSPITAL.

15:07.407 --> 15:12.182
IT'S SNOWY AND QUIET...
COLD...

15:12.182 --> 15:14.384
AND PERFECT.

15:14.384 --> 15:18.248
SO, YOU KNOW, YOU JUST GOTTA
MAKE IT UNTIL NEW YEAR'S EVE.

15:20.320 --> 15:22.322
I NEED TO GO OUTSIDE.

15:22.322 --> 15:24.424
WHAT?
WHAT?

15:24.424 --> 15:26.426
I MIGHT DIE.
WE ALL KNOW THAT.

15:26.426 --> 15:28.428
I MIGHT DIE REALLY SOON.

15:28.428 --> 15:33.233
BUT SNOW IS MY FAVORITE THING
IN THE WHOLE WIDE WORLD.

15:33.233 --> 15:36.066
IT'S MY FAVORITE THING.

15:36.066 --> 15:38.368
PLEASE.

15:38.368 --> 15:41.011
PLEASE, OKAY?

15:41.011 --> 15:43.073
I'M SORRY, BUT--
WE CAN DO THAT.

15:47.247 --> 15:49.279
WE CAN DO THAT.

15:52.222 --> 15:55.155
I WANT TO BOLT.
I WANT TO QUIT.

15:55.155 --> 15:57.057
I WANT TO...
GO BACK TO NEW YORK

15:57.057 --> 16:00.060
OR I DON'T KNOW--ARKANSAS--

16:00.060 --> 16:02.392
SOMEWHERE NO ONE CAN COME
LOOKING FOR ME.

16:02.392 --> 16:04.394
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO TALK TO HER. I...

16:04.394 --> 16:06.736
AND I DON'T KNOW
WHAT SHE WANTS FROM ME.

16:06.736 --> 16:09.039
IT'S THE GUILT, YOU KNOW?

16:09.039 --> 16:12.072
IT'S LIKE EVERY TIME
I LOOK AT HER, IT JUST...

16:12.072 --> 16:15.505
(sighs) THE GUILT IS LIKE
A PUNCH IN THE GUT EVERY DAY.

16:15.505 --> 16:18.978
WELL, YOU SHOULDN'T
FEEL GUILTY. YOU DIDN'T KNOW.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.011
I DID KNOW.

16:21.011 --> 16:24.254
I KNEW WHEN HER MOM
GOT PREGNANT.

16:24.254 --> 16:26.316
SHE TOLD ME.

16:26.316 --> 16:28.318
I GAVE HER
A COUPLE HUNDRED BUCKS

16:28.318 --> 16:31.561
AND I LEFT TOWN,
AND I NEVER SAW HER AGAIN.

16:31.561 --> 16:35.495
YOU KNOW, I FIGURED SHE GOT
AN ABORTION. HOPED.

16:35.495 --> 16:37.767
BUT I DID KNOW.

16:37.767 --> 16:39.329
(beeping)

16:39.329 --> 16:41.331
WELL, YOU'RE
A DIFFERENT GUY NOW.

16:41.331 --> 16:43.403
YOU'RE NOT 18 ANYMORE.
YOU'VE GROWN-UP.

16:43.403 --> 16:46.676
YOU'RE CAPABLE OF BETTER.

16:46.676 --> 16:49.679
NICHOLAS IS BACK IN THE E.R.
HE'S GOT A NOSEBLEED, BAD.

16:49.679 --> 16:52.442
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO STOP IT
FOR AN HOUR.
WE CAN'T OPERATE.
WE'RE NOT READY.

16:52.442 --> 16:56.116
ALL RIGHT, WELL, THEN I'LL
ADMIT HIM AND KEEP TRANSFUSING

16:56.116 --> 17:00.490
UNTIL THE EQUIPMENT'S DONE,
WHICH IS GONNA BE SOON, I HOPE?

17:00.490 --> 17:02.722
♪♪

17:02.722 --> 17:05.695
UM, HELLO.
ARE YOU BAILEY'S--

17:05.695 --> 17:07.697
OR I MEAN, MIRANDA'S DAD?

17:07.697 --> 17:10.200
WILLIAM BAILEY.
UH, YOU CAN CALL ME BILL.

17:10.200 --> 17:11.701
OKAY. HI, BILL.

17:11.701 --> 17:14.664
I'M CALLIE TORRES.
I'M A-A FRIEND OF BAILEY'S.

17:14.664 --> 17:17.036
SHE MENTIONED THAT
SHE SNUCK YOU IN HERE.

17:17.036 --> 17:20.610
SAID I SHOULD COME SAY HI.
SO WHAT'S THAT
SHE'S DOING DOWN THERE?

17:20.610 --> 17:22.212
OH, THAT'S A HERNIA REPAIR.

17:22.212 --> 17:24.414
WE GET A LOT OF HERNIAS
AT CHRISTMAS.

17:24.414 --> 17:26.716
LOTS OF PEOPLE LIFTING TREES
OR HEAVY GIFTS

17:26.716 --> 17:28.518
OR SANTA BAGS.

17:28.518 --> 17:31.751
IT'S--OH, WE GET A LOT
OF BROKEN BONES, TOO,

17:31.751 --> 17:33.783
'CAUSE OF THE WEATHER.

17:33.783 --> 17:35.785
OH, I HAD THIS, UH,
THIS GUY EARLIER.

17:35.785 --> 17:38.057
HE GOT AN ELECTRIC SHOCK
FROM SOME CHRISTMAS LIGHTS.

17:38.057 --> 17:41.791
THE SHOCK WAS SO BIG THAT IT
BROKE BOTH OF HIS WRISTS.
WHOA.

17:41.791 --> 17:44.334
YEAH. ANYWAY,
I'M DATING WOMEN AND--

17:44.334 --> 17:46.266
UH, I'M SORRY?

17:46.266 --> 17:50.600
OH, I'M, UH... I'VE RECENTLY
STARTED DATING WOMEN.

17:50.600 --> 17:54.104
AND MY FAMILY HAD A REALLY
HARD TIME ACCEPTING THAT,

17:54.104 --> 17:56.406
BUT, YOU KNOW,
WE WORKED THROUGH IT.

17:56.406 --> 17:58.808
AND, UM...

17:58.808 --> 18:00.810
BAILEY SAID
THAT YOU'RE HAVING

18:00.810 --> 18:02.812
A HARD TIME
WITH HER DIVORCE,

18:02.812 --> 18:05.415
WHICH I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND.

18:05.415 --> 18:07.417
BUT I... I J--

18:07.417 --> 18:09.419
I WANTED TO SAY THAT

18:09.419 --> 18:11.821
SHE DIDN'T COME
TO THAT DECISION LIGHTLY.

18:11.821 --> 18:15.695
AND SHE'S A GOOD PERSON,
AND...

18:15.695 --> 18:18.228
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

18:18.228 --> 18:19.799
♪♪

18:19.799 --> 18:21.801
DID HUNT EVER TELL YOU
ABOUT THE TIME

18:21.801 --> 18:24.504
THAT HE MADE SNOW?
NO.

18:24.504 --> 18:26.506
HIS GUYS WERE FEELING
THE HOLIDAYS PRETTY BAD,

18:26.506 --> 18:29.509
SO HUNT ORDERS ONE OF THOSE
SNOW MAKERS ON CHRISTMAS EVE.

18:29.509 --> 18:31.511
HE TRIES
TO GET THE THING GOING,

18:31.511 --> 18:34.514
BUT THE MINUTE THAT THE SNOW
HIT THE SAND, IT MELTS.

18:34.514 --> 18:37.347
SO HUNT
BLINDFOLDED HIS GUYS

18:37.347 --> 18:39.349
AND MADE THEM
PUT THEIR FACES

18:39.349 --> 18:41.851
RIGHT UP
TO THE SNOWBLOWER.

18:41.851 --> 18:44.594
THERE WAS THIS ONE KID
FROM MINNESOTA.

18:44.594 --> 18:46.256
HE ACTUALLY CRIED.

18:46.256 --> 18:50.200
HE SAID IT FELT EXACTLY
LIKE CHRISTMAS AT HOME.

18:50.200 --> 18:52.332
(man) ♪ ALL THAT I WANT... ♪

18:52.332 --> 18:53.863
HUH.

18:53.863 --> 18:57.367
(Jackson with lowered voice)
OOH, HUNT.

18:57.367 --> 19:00.640
HUNT'S SO DELICIOUS WHEN HE'S
TENDING TO BLOODY SOLDIERS.

19:00.640 --> 19:02.212
LOVE ME SOME HUNT.

19:02.212 --> 19:04.143
SHUT UP. WHAT ARE YOU...

19:04.143 --> 19:07.377
♪ EVERY FRONT YARD
IS DREAMY ♪

19:07.377 --> 19:10.149
SO HOW WAS THE VIEW?

19:10.149 --> 19:12.822
♪ PLASTIC SANTAS AND SLEIGHS ♪

19:12.822 --> 19:14.824
I HAVE BEEN A PROUD FATHER.

19:14.824 --> 19:18.858
YOUR WHOLE LIFE,
I HAVE BEEN A PROUD FATHER.

19:18.858 --> 19:20.860
YOUR MOTHER AND I
SAT IN THE FRONT ROW

19:20.860 --> 19:24.864
OF EVERY DANCE CLASS,
EVERY OBOE RECITAL,

19:24.864 --> 19:26.566
AND WE CHEERED.

19:26.566 --> 19:28.568
WE SAT IN THE FRONT ROW
OF EVERY GRADUATION.

19:28.568 --> 19:30.870
I WAS ALWAYS THE FIRST ONE
ON MY FEET

19:30.870 --> 19:32.902
AND THE LOUDEST ONE
IN THE CROWD.

19:32.902 --> 19:37.647
I HAVE BEEN...
A PROUD FATHER.

19:37.647 --> 19:38.948
(chuckles)

19:38.948 --> 19:42.181
AND TODAY, MIRANDA,
I-I S-SAT IN THE GALLERY,

19:42.181 --> 19:46.185
AND I WATCHED YOU REPAIR
SOME FAT MAN'S HERNIA.

19:46.185 --> 19:48.758
AND FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN MY LIFE,

19:48.758 --> 19:51.221
I FELT ASHAMED OF YOU.

19:51.221 --> 19:52.792
♪ ALL THAT I WANT... ♪

19:52.792 --> 19:55.225
THIS IS WHAT YOU DO
ON CHRISTMAS?

19:55.225 --> 19:58.228
FOR THIS,
YOU TRADED YOUR HUSBAND?

19:58.228 --> 20:01.931
FOR THIS, YOU TRADED
YOUR CHILD'S FAMILY?

20:01.931 --> 20:03.933
SO YOU COULD WORK ALL DAY

20:03.933 --> 20:06.236
AND GO HOME ALONE
ON CHRISTMAS

20:06.236 --> 20:11.541
TO AN EMPTY HOUSE
WITHOUT EVEN A TREE.

20:11.541 --> 20:15.285
I HAVE BEEN A PROUD FATHER...

20:15.285 --> 20:16.786
MIRANDA.

20:16.786 --> 20:18.788
BUT I WOULD BE
A BAD FATHER TODAY

20:18.788 --> 20:20.790
IF I DIDN'T LOOK YOU
IN THE EYE

20:20.790 --> 20:25.255
AND TELL YOU THAT YOU
HAVE MADE A TERRIBLE MISTAKE.

20:25.255 --> 20:28.558
YOU BROKE YOUR FAMILY.

20:28.558 --> 20:32.231
YOU SET YOUR SON UP TO FAIL.

20:32.231 --> 20:34.734
AND THE CHILD I RAISED...

20:34.734 --> 20:38.938
HUH, SHE WAS RAISED
BETTER THAN THAT.

20:38.938 --> 20:44.414
♪ SNOW FALLS LOW
IN THE MOONLIGHT ♪
♪ SNOW FALLS LOW
IN THE MOONLIGHT ♪

20:44.414 --> 20:50.249
♪ CHILDREN MERRILY PLAY ♪
♪ CHILDREN MERRILY PLAY ♪

20:50.249 --> 20:53.022
WELL, THAT'S SOMETHING
YOU DON'T SEE EVERY DAY.

20:53.022 --> 20:55.785
SHE COULD CODE.
THE MONITOR COULD SHORT OUT.

20:55.785 --> 20:57.287
TEDDY'S A BRILLIANT SURGEON,

20:57.287 --> 20:59.258
BUT I-I DON'T GET
HOW SHE MADE THIS CALL.

20:59.258 --> 21:01.331
I GET IT.
IT'S PATIENT CARE.

21:01.331 --> 21:04.394
AND TEDDY'S ALWAYS BEEN
A SUCKER FOR CHRISTMAS.

21:09.569 --> 21:12.372
♪ ALL THAT I WANT ♪

21:12.372 --> 21:15.345
♪ FOR CHRISTMAS ♪

21:15.345 --> 21:21.511
♪ IS TO GIVE MY LOVE AWAY ♪

21:24.614 --> 21:27.917
(man) OH, MY GOD. KELSEY!

21:35.565 --> 21:37.527
FROM YOUR X-RAYS AND C.T.,

21:37.527 --> 21:39.699
IT LOOKS LIKE PART OF
YOUR BOWEL HAS DIED.

21:39.699 --> 21:42.332
IT--IT'S A SIDE EFFECT
OF YOUR POOR CIRCULATION.

21:42.332 --> 21:43.973
IT'S WHY YOU COLLAPSED.

21:43.973 --> 21:47.577
BUT JUST...
FIX HER, OKAY?

21:47.577 --> 21:49.979
SHE CAN'T
HAVE COME THIS FAR TO...

21:49.979 --> 21:52.382
JUST FIX HER.
(mouths word)

21:54.043 --> 21:57.517
WE'RE GONNA NEED TO REPAIR
THIS AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

21:57.517 --> 22:00.720
THE MORE TIME WE WAIT,
THE MORE BOWEL DIES.
YEAH, BUT HOW?

22:00.720 --> 22:03.723
SHE'S SEPTIC, HYPOTENSIVE,
AND SHE HAS NO HEART.

22:03.723 --> 22:06.055
(Teddy) HER PRESSURE'S TOO LOW
FOR GENERAL ANESTHESIA.

22:06.055 --> 22:08.057
SHE WON'T SURVIVE.

22:08.057 --> 22:13.032
THEN... WE WON'T
PUT HER UNDER GENERAL.

22:13.032 --> 22:16.035
ANDTHIS GOES THROUGH THE NOSE
TO THE BASE OF THE SKULL,

22:16.035 --> 22:18.037
AND THEN I DRILL
THE BONE OFF.

22:18.037 --> 22:21.040
WELL, WHAT HAPPENS
ONCE YOU DRILL THE HOLES?
WE PUT
MINIATURE STAPLE CLIPS

22:21.040 --> 22:23.072
ON THE VESSELS.
WITH WHAT INSTRUMENT?

22:23.072 --> 22:26.746
WE DON'T HAVE IT. NOT YET.
BUT WE WILL. WE WILL.

22:26.746 --> 22:29.779
WE'RE, UH, STILL TRYING TO
FIGURE OUT HOW TO BUILD IT,

22:29.779 --> 22:31.080
BUT WE'RE ON IT.

22:31.080 --> 22:32.952
UH... I WOULD LIKE

22:32.952 --> 22:35.925
AN INVITATION TO YOUR HOME
FOR CHRISTMAS DINNER.

22:35.925 --> 22:38.758
I KNOW IT'S VERY LATE FOR ME

22:38.758 --> 22:40.790
TO BE ASKING
FOR SUCH AN INVITATION,

22:40.790 --> 22:43.032
GIVEN THAT IT IS, IN FACT,
CHRISTMAS DAY.

22:43.032 --> 22:44.994
HOWEVER, I HAVE
A VERY WORRIED FATHER,

22:44.994 --> 22:47.997
AND IF I DON'T LOOK LIKE
I HAVE SOME SORT OF LIFE,

22:47.997 --> 22:50.770
HE'LL NEVER LEAVE.

22:50.770 --> 22:53.903
I HAVE A BOWEL INFARCTION
TO REPAIR, AND THEN AFTER THAT,

22:53.903 --> 22:56.045
I'LL BE FREE
TO COME TO YOUR HOME.
SOUNDS FINE.

22:56.045 --> 22:58.377
OH, ABSOLUTELY.
THANK YOU.

22:58.377 --> 23:00.980
THE CHIEF JUST CUT OFF
THE FUNDING FOR OUR EQUIPMENT.
WHAT?

23:00.980 --> 23:02.652
WHAT?
WE'RE WAY OVER BUDGET,

23:02.652 --> 23:04.914
AND NICHOLAS
IS RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

23:04.914 --> 23:07.817
WE WANT OUR BONUSES TO GO
TOWARDS FINISHING THE PROTOTYPE

23:07.817 --> 23:09.989
FOR NICHOLAS JACOBSEN.
SORRY. YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

23:09.989 --> 23:12.922
NO, BUT IT'LL BE LIKE
A DONATION.
THEY'RE OUR BONUSES.

23:15.965 --> 23:19.899
THERE ARE NO BONUSES.
THAT'S WHAT HE'S TRYING TO SAY.

23:19.899 --> 23:23.102
THERE ARE NO BONUSES
THIS YEAR. I'M SORRY.

23:23.102 --> 23:25.575
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

23:25.575 --> 23:27.577
(sighs)

23:31.080 --> 23:33.483
I'LL WRITE A CHECK.
HOW MUCH?

23:36.816 --> 23:39.619
I'LL SPLIT IT WITH YOU.
THANK YOU.

23:43.022 --> 23:47.156
I HAVE A TEENAGER. WHAT IF
SHE WANTS TO GO TO COLLEGE?
HAVE YOU MET HER?

23:47.156 --> 23:49.158
FINE, I'M IN.

23:49.158 --> 23:53.162
THANK YOU. I'LL GET BACK TO
YOU WITH NUMBERS. UH, SHEP.

23:53.162 --> 23:55.565
CHIEF.

23:55.565 --> 23:57.867
I'M SORRY
I TRIED TO FIRE YOU.

23:57.867 --> 24:02.111
AND IN THE SPIRIT
OF THE HOLIDAYS, I WAS, UH...

24:02.111 --> 24:03.843
SORRY.

24:06.976 --> 24:10.750
("Baby, It's Cold Outside"
playing on guitar)

24:14.153 --> 24:16.025
♪ I REALLY CAN'T STAY ♪

24:16.025 --> 24:18.457
♪ BUT, BABY,
IT'S COLD OUTSIDE ♪

24:18.457 --> 24:19.929
♪ I'VE GOT TO GO 'WAY ♪

24:19.929 --> 24:23.493
♪ BUT, BABY,
IT'S COLD OUTSIDE ♪

24:23.493 --> 24:25.194
♪ THIS EVENING HAS BEEN ♪
♪ BEEN ♪

24:25.194 --> 24:28.768
♪ SO VERY NICE ♪
♪ HOPIN' YOU WOULD
DROP IN ♪

24:28.768 --> 24:30.570
♪ I'LL HOLD YOUR HANDS ♪

24:30.570 --> 24:33.072
♪ THEY'RE LIKE ICE ♪
♪ MY MOTHER
WILL START TO WORRY ♪

24:33.072 --> 24:34.944
♪ HEY, BEAUTIFUL,
WHAT'S YOUR HURRY? ♪

24:34.944 --> 24:36.946
♪ MY FATHER WILL BE
PACING THE FLOOR ♪

24:36.946 --> 24:38.948
♪ LISTEN TO THE FIRE ROAR ♪

24:38.948 --> 24:42.251
♪ SO REALLY,
I'D BETTER SCURRY ♪

24:42.251 --> 24:44.253
♪ WELL, MAYBE JUST
A HALF A DRINK MORE... ♪

24:44.253 --> 24:47.917
YOU'RE NOT SERIOUS. YOU GOT HIM
A SNOW GLOBE OF SEATTLE?

24:47.917 --> 24:49.218
WHAT? HE LIKES SEATTLE.

24:49.218 --> 24:51.961
I GAVE YOU 50 BUCKS.
WHERE'S MY CHANGE?

24:51.961 --> 24:53.262
UM... (clears throat)

24:53.262 --> 24:57.727
MARK...
YOUR KIDS ARE BICKERING.

24:57.727 --> 24:59.729
HAVE YOU
TALKED TO HER YET?

24:59.729 --> 25:01.971
I'M WORKIN' ON IT.

25:01.971 --> 25:03.673
MM.

25:03.673 --> 25:06.075
YOUR SISTER'S GOT
A READY-MADE FAMILY THERE.

25:06.075 --> 25:08.578
WELL, DON'T WORRY.
SHE DIDN'T FORGET ABOUT YOU.

25:08.578 --> 25:10.740
SHE INVITED YOU, RIGHT?

25:10.740 --> 25:13.142
(chuckles)
(Arizona and Richard
continue singing indistinctly)

25:13.142 --> 25:16.986
HE'S DRINKING... ISN'T HE?

25:16.986 --> 25:18.517
RICHARD.

25:18.517 --> 25:21.150
HE'S OFF THE WAGON.

25:21.150 --> 25:23.152
WELL, HE'S DRINKING EGGNOG.
IT'S CHRISTMAS.

25:23.152 --> 25:25.995
EVERYBODY DRINKS EGGNOG
AT CHRISTMAS.

25:25.995 --> 25:29.028
MM, SOME PEOPLE DO.
RECOVERING ALCOHOLICS DON'T.

25:29.028 --> 25:31.030
HE'S NOT AN ALCOHOLIC.

25:31.030 --> 25:33.102
THAT WAS A MISDIAGNOSIS.

25:33.102 --> 25:34.804
(singing continues)

25:34.804 --> 25:37.567
IS THAT
WHAT HE'S TELLING YOU?

25:37.567 --> 25:40.570
MEREDITH, HE IS A SURGEON
AND HE IS DRINKING,

25:40.570 --> 25:42.572
AND HE IS AN ALCOHOLIC.

25:42.572 --> 25:45.214
THAT COULD QUICKLY
BECOME CATASTROPHIC.

25:45.214 --> 25:47.016
(singing continues)

25:47.016 --> 25:49.218
WERE YOU DRINKING
WHEN I WAS A KID,

25:49.218 --> 25:51.851
WHEN YOU LEFT ME
WITH MY MOTHER

25:51.851 --> 25:55.224
AND GOT ANOTHER FAMILY
AND NEVER LOOKED BACK?

25:55.224 --> 25:57.757
(singing continues)

25:57.757 --> 26:00.089
NO. (sighs)

26:00.089 --> 26:03.833
NO, I DIDN'T START DRINKING
TILL MUCH LATER.

26:03.833 --> 26:06.135
WELL, THEN WE CAN'T BLAME
THE WORLD'S EVILS

26:06.135 --> 26:09.098
ON ALCOHOL, CAN WE?

26:09.098 --> 26:16.005
(Arizona and Richard)
♪ OH, BUT IT'S COLD OUTSIDE ♪

26:16.005 --> 26:17.246
(laughter)

26:19.048 --> 26:21.751
(deepened voice) OH, YEAH.
(Arizona and Owen laugh)

26:21.751 --> 26:23.913
IT HURTS.
I KNOW.

26:23.913 --> 26:27.617
SURGERY WITH ONLY A LOCAL
ANESTHETIC IS NOT IDEAL.

26:27.617 --> 26:30.159
HANG IN THERE.
(Kelsey moans)

26:30.159 --> 26:32.121
MM.
(Miranda) OKAY, OKAY.

26:32.121 --> 26:34.093
(groans)
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

26:34.093 --> 26:36.966
I'M HERE WITH YOU,
ALL RIGHT?
(cries)

26:36.966 --> 26:41.130
HEY, HEY. HEY, NO TEARS.
NO TEARS AT CHRISTMAS.

26:41.130 --> 26:43.903
NO, THERE'S ONLY, UH,

26:43.903 --> 26:46.936
LIGHTS AND, UM, SNOWMEN...

26:46.936 --> 26:48.978
(moans)
AND SONGS.

26:48.978 --> 26:50.980
UM...

26:50.980 --> 26:54.814
♪ OH, THE WEATHER OUTSIDE
IS FRIGHTFUL ♪

26:54.814 --> 26:57.787
♪ BUT THE FIRE
IS SO DELIGHTFUL ♪

26:57.787 --> 26:59.849
COME ON NOW.

26:59.849 --> 27:02.121
♪ BUT SINCE
WE'VE NO PLACE TO GO ♪
♪ BUT SINCE
WE'VE NO PLACE TO GO ♪

27:02.121 --> 27:03.292
KAREV.

27:03.292 --> 27:04.924
NO, THANKS.

27:04.924 --> 27:08.197
SING, YANG.
OH, NO. I DON'T--
UM, I'M JEWISH.

27:08.197 --> 27:10.199
HEY, DON'T PLAY
THE RACE CARD WITH ME.

27:10.199 --> 27:12.702
SING OR GET OFF MY SERVICE.

27:12.702 --> 27:16.135
♪ LET IT SNOW, LET IT SNOW,
LET IT SNOW ♪

27:16.135 --> 27:19.638
(all) ♪ IT DOESN'T SHOW SIGNS
OF STOPPING ♪

27:19.638 --> 27:23.713
♪ AND I'VE BROUGHT
SOME CORN FOR POPPING ♪

27:23.713 --> 27:25.014
YOU, TOO, KAREV.

27:25.014 --> 27:27.977
♪ THE LIGHTS ARE TURNED
WAY DOWN LOW ♪

27:27.977 --> 27:32.922
♪ LET IT SNOW, LET IT SNOW,
LET IT SNOW ♪

27:32.922 --> 27:36.225
(woman)
♪ SILENT NIGHT ♪

27:36.225 --> 27:38.988
(Lexie) THE HOUSE
LOOKS BEAUTIFUL, MER.
THANK YOU.

27:38.988 --> 27:40.329
CALLIE?

27:40.329 --> 27:42.862
WORKING.
OH, THAT'S TOO BAD.

27:42.862 --> 27:45.294
HERE,
YOU WANT SOME STUFFING?
THANKS.

27:45.294 --> 27:47.997
(Owen)
THAT'S ALL, THANK YOU.
OH, HOW--HOW'D KELSEY DO?

27:47.997 --> 27:50.299
UH, WELL.
WHO'S KELSEY?

27:50.299 --> 27:53.002
A GIRL WITH NO HEART.

27:53.002 --> 27:55.074
I HAD TO DO A LAPAROSCOPIC
BOWEL REPAIR

27:55.074 --> 27:57.777
WHILE THE POOR THING
WAS AWAKE ON THE TABLE.

27:57.777 --> 28:00.049
MIRANDA,
MIND YOUR MANNERS.

28:00.049 --> 28:03.082
EVEN IF SURGERY IS YOUR
WHOLE LIFE, IT DOESN'T MEAN

28:03.082 --> 28:07.156
YOU HAVE TO TALK ABOUT BOWELS
AT THE DINNER TABLE.

28:07.156 --> 28:13.122
♪ ...HEAVENLY PEACE ♪

28:13.122 --> 28:17.066
♪ SLEEP IN HEAVENLY PEACE ♪

28:17.066 --> 28:20.930
MY CHILD IS HEALTHY.

28:20.930 --> 28:23.402
EXCUSE ME?

28:23.402 --> 28:27.937
HE MAY NOT BE WITH ME TONIGHT,
BUT HE'S HEALTHY...

28:27.937 --> 28:31.010
I DIDN'T SAY HE--
AND HE'S WELL-LOVED.
HE'S A WELL-LOVED BOY.

28:31.010 --> 28:32.812
AND HE'S A HAPPY BOY.

28:32.812 --> 28:35.484
AND STAYING
IN AN UNHAPPY MARRIAGE--

28:35.484 --> 28:37.486
NOW IS NOT THE TIME
OR THE PLACE--

28:37.486 --> 28:41.090
STAYING IN AN UNHAPPY MARRIAGE,
A MARRIAGE THAT I'VE OUTGROWN,

28:41.090 --> 28:47.126
A MARRIAGE FULL OF ULTIMATUMS
AND NUMBNESS AND RESENTMENT--

28:47.126 --> 28:48.858
MIRANDA--

28:48.858 --> 28:51.130
(voice breaking) THAT IS NOT
THE KIND OF LIFE

28:51.130 --> 28:53.132
I WANT TO MODEL
FOR MY CHILD.

28:53.132 --> 28:55.434
THAT IS NOT WHAT
I WANT HIM TO BELIEVE

28:55.434 --> 28:58.367
MARRIED LOVE IS.

28:58.367 --> 29:01.010
LOOK, I KNOW WHAT'S POSSIBLE.

29:01.010 --> 29:03.012
I KNOW
WHAT'S OUT THERE FOR ME

29:03.012 --> 29:05.214
BECAUSE YOU TAUGHT ME WELL.

29:05.214 --> 29:09.919
YOU AND MOM SHOWED ME
WHAT TRUE LOVE LOOKS LIKE.

29:09.919 --> 29:12.922
SO I CHOSE NOT TO SETTLE,
AND I'M HAPPIER FOR IT,

29:12.922 --> 29:15.925
EVEN IF I'M ALONE
AT CHRISTMAS.

29:15.925 --> 29:20.329
MY CHILD IS HEALTHY,
AND I'M HAPPY.

29:20.329 --> 29:24.834
♪ RADIANT BEAMS ♪

29:24.834 --> 29:28.337
♪ FROM THY HOLY FACE ♪

29:28.337 --> 29:31.941
♪ WITH THE DAWN ♪

29:31.941 --> 29:34.103
OF REDEEMING GRACE ♪

29:34.103 --> 29:36.375
MM.

29:36.375 --> 29:40.149
♪ JESUS, LORD, AT THY BIRTH ♪

29:40.149 --> 29:42.451
AND, YOU KNOW,
PART OF MY HAPPINESS IS

29:42.451 --> 29:46.355
THE FACT THAT I GOT TO REPAIR
A WOMAN'S BOWEL

29:46.355 --> 29:48.557
AND SAVE HER LIFE TODAY.

29:48.557 --> 29:50.489
AND THAT'S GOD'S WORK,

29:50.489 --> 29:55.124
WHICH MAKES THIS APPROPRIATE
CHRISTMAS DINNER CONVERSATION.

29:55.124 --> 29:57.096
YEAH.

29:57.096 --> 30:00.499
♪ HOLY NIGHT ♪

30:00.499 --> 30:04.173
♪ SON OF GOD ♪

30:04.173 --> 30:06.936
(crying) I'M HAPPY.

30:06.936 --> 30:09.008
AND MY CHILD IS HEALTHY.

30:09.008 --> 30:12.111
AND THAT'S ENOUGH
FOR ME TODAY, DAD.

30:12.111 --> 30:14.243
THAT'S ENOUGH.

30:14.243 --> 30:17.346
♪ WITH THE DAWN OF ♪

30:17.346 --> 30:22.191
♪ REDEEMING GRACE ♪

30:22.191 --> 30:24.123
♪ JESUS, LORD... ♪

30:24.123 --> 30:26.195
UH, GREEN BEANS, ANYONE?

30:26.195 --> 30:27.496
THANK YOU.

30:27.496 --> 30:29.528
(clears throat)

30:29.528 --> 30:31.060
THANKS.

30:31.060 --> 30:33.262
♪ JESUS, LORD ♪

30:33.262 --> 30:37.366
♪ AT THY BIRTH ♪

30:45.514 --> 30:48.017
("Have Yourself a Merry
Little Christmas" playing)

30:48.017 --> 30:49.318
(Richard) OKAY.

30:49.318 --> 30:52.151
HERE I WOULD ADVISE
A ONE-HAND TIE.

30:54.223 --> 30:58.857
(man) ♪ HAVE YOURSELF
A MERRY... ♪

30:58.857 --> 31:02.431
UM, OKAY. UH, WHY DON'T I TALK
AND YOU OPERATE?
GOOD.

31:02.431 --> 31:03.632
♪♪

31:03.632 --> 31:06.165
LAST NIGHT
WAS MY LAST DRINK.

31:06.165 --> 31:09.298
THE SHAKING WILL STOP SOON.
GOOD. GOOD FOR YOU.

31:09.298 --> 31:12.271
THAT DOESN'T MEAN I HAVE TO
QUIT DRINKING TEQUILA, DOES IT?

31:12.271 --> 31:15.044
(chuckles)
'CAUSE I REALLY LIKE TEQUILA.

31:15.044 --> 31:17.476
♪ ...WILL BE OUT OF SIGHT ♪

31:17.476 --> 31:20.109
(lowered voice)
IT'S NEW YEAR'S EVE.

31:20.109 --> 31:22.111
(lowered voice) I KNOW.

31:22.111 --> 31:25.154
SHE SHOWS NO SIGNS OF LEAVING--
NO SUITCASE PACKED, NOTHING.

31:25.154 --> 31:29.288
(whispers) TALK TO HER RIGHT
NOW, OR NO MORE SEX FOR YOU.

31:29.288 --> 31:30.589
(exhales deeply)

31:30.589 --> 31:33.192
♪♪

31:33.192 --> 31:35.324
SO...

31:35.324 --> 31:38.127
WHAT YOU READING?

31:38.127 --> 31:43.172
♪ MAKE THE YULETIDE GAY ♪

31:43.172 --> 31:45.674
I CAN TELL YOU DON'T
REALLY LIKE ME,

31:45.674 --> 31:48.677
AND, UM, YOUR GIRLFRIEND'S,
LIKE, TOTALLY FREAKED OUT BY ME

31:48.677 --> 31:51.040
'CAUSE I'M KINDA, LIKE,
HOTTER THAN HER.

31:51.040 --> 31:54.443
BUT I'M PREGNANT. YEAH.

31:54.443 --> 31:56.445
I'M HAVING A BABY, AND, UM,

31:56.445 --> 31:58.447
THAT'S WHY
I DROPPED OUT OF SCHOOL

31:58.447 --> 32:01.590
AND THAT'S WHY
MY MOM KICKED ME OUT.

32:01.590 --> 32:03.953
LOOK...

32:03.953 --> 32:06.095
I KNOW YOU DON'T
OWE ME ANYTHING...

32:06.095 --> 32:09.098
BUT I CAN TELL YOU GUYS
ARE ABOUT TO KICK ME OUT...

32:09.098 --> 32:11.330
(voice breaking)
AND I... I...

32:11.330 --> 32:13.932
I DON'T HAVE
ANYWHERE ELSE TO GO.

32:13.932 --> 32:15.164
SHH. SHH.

32:15.164 --> 32:17.166
(sniffles and cries)

32:17.166 --> 32:19.168
IT'S OKAY.

32:19.168 --> 32:22.241
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

32:22.241 --> 32:26.115
(crying)

32:26.115 --> 32:28.377
♪♪

32:28.377 --> 32:31.120
HE'S IN HYPOVOLEMIC SHOCK.
HE'S LOST TOO MUCH BLOOD.

32:31.120 --> 32:34.323
AND I DIDN'T WANT TO HAVE TO
DO THIS, BUT WE'RE GONNA

32:34.323 --> 32:37.486
HAVE TO PUT A TUBE DOWN HIS
THROAT TO HELP HIM BREATHE.
NICHOLAS.

32:37.486 --> 32:40.189
WE NEED TO TUBE HIM RIGHT NOW.
DON'T TUBE HIM. BAG HIM
TILL WE GET TO THE O.R.

32:40.189 --> 32:42.291
THE O.R.?
WE FINISHED THE INSTRUMENTS.

32:42.291 --> 32:45.094
(Arizona) WE DID?
YEAH, WE'RE GONNA OPERATE.

32:45.094 --> 32:47.266
I JUST NEED YOU TO SIGN
A CONSENT FORM.
PRETTY DRAMATIC TIMING,
DR. SHEPHERD.

32:47.266 --> 32:49.598
I LIKE TO MAKE AN ENTRANCE.
IT'S OKAY.

32:49.598 --> 32:52.601
(lowered voice) HER KIDNEYS
ARE SHUTTING DOWN.

32:52.601 --> 32:56.605
WE NEED TO FIND A DONOR.
WE NEEDED TO FIND ONE YESTERDAY.

32:59.108 --> 33:02.411
IT'S NEW YEAR'S EVE,
DR. YANG.

33:02.411 --> 33:06.355
YOU SAID I JUST HAD TO MAKE IT
TO NEW YEAR'S EVE.

33:06.355 --> 33:10.159
DRUNKS ALL OVER THE ROADS.
SO YEAH.

33:10.159 --> 33:12.161
TONIGHT'S ARE BEST SHOT.

33:12.161 --> 33:15.164
(pop version of "The Little
Drummer Boy" playing)

33:18.297 --> 33:20.629
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

33:20.629 --> 33:22.501
(man) ♪ COME... ♪

33:22.501 --> 33:24.233
OH, HOW'S IT HANDLING?

33:24.233 --> 33:27.036
IT COULD BEND
A LITTLE MORE GENTLY.

33:27.036 --> 33:30.409
DON'T GET ALL CRITICAL.
THING COST ME A FORTUNE.

33:30.409 --> 33:34.143
I COULD USE ONE MORE DAY
TO PRACTICE. OKAY.

33:34.143 --> 33:37.386
INSERTING THE CLIP APPLIER.

33:37.386 --> 33:39.518
♪♪

33:39.518 --> 33:43.352
WHY DON'T YOU TRY
TORQUING IT A LITTLE

33:43.352 --> 33:45.494
TO GET A DIFFERENT ANGLE?

33:45.494 --> 33:47.656
THERE YOU GO.

33:47.656 --> 33:50.299
OKAY. THERE IT IS.

33:50.299 --> 33:51.430
PERFECT.

33:51.430 --> 33:53.632
OKAY.

33:53.632 --> 33:55.804
♪ RUM PUM PUM PUM ♪

33:55.804 --> 34:00.539
♪ RUM PUM PUM PUM ♪

34:00.539 --> 34:04.443
♪ SO TO HONOR HIM ♪

34:04.443 --> 34:07.216
♪ PA RUM PUM PUM PUM ♪

34:07.216 --> 34:10.349
GOT IT.
THAT'S THE LAST CLIP.

34:10.349 --> 34:13.252
OH, MY GOD!
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
WE'RE DONE HERE.

34:13.252 --> 34:16.125
NICE WORK. BEAUTIFUL.
(Meredith)
OH, MY GOD. YOU DID IT.

34:16.125 --> 34:18.127
(Lexie) AMAZING.

34:18.127 --> 34:20.229
HANG ON. LOOK AT THE CLOCK.

34:20.229 --> 34:22.261
AND THAT'S, UH, SEVEN, SIX...

34:22.261 --> 34:24.663
(all) FIVE, FOUR...

34:24.663 --> 34:27.166
THREE, TWO, ONE.

34:27.166 --> 34:29.668
HAPPY NEW YEAR!

34:29.668 --> 34:31.400
HAPPY NEW YEAR.

34:31.400 --> 34:34.743
HAPPY NEW YEAR.
HAPPY NEW YEAR.

34:34.743 --> 34:36.275
MWAH.

34:36.275 --> 34:38.547
♪ PA RUM PUM PUM PUM ♪

34:38.547 --> 34:40.509
♪ ON MY DRUM ♪

34:40.509 --> 34:43.212
I'M JUST
GONNA TAKE A LISTEN.

34:48.257 --> 34:53.122
♪ MARY NODDED ♪

34:53.122 --> 34:55.324
♪ PA RUM PUM PUM PUM ♪

34:58.167 --> 35:01.530
♪ THE OX AND LAMB KEPT TIME ♪

35:01.530 --> 35:04.633
♪ PA RUM PUM PUM PUM ♪

35:04.633 --> 35:07.606
IT LOOKS LIKE WE'RE HITTING
THE FINAL WAVE.
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

35:07.606 --> 35:10.639
YEAH, WELL, I'M HEADED TO THE--
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?
YOU.

35:10.639 --> 35:13.111
ME?
YEAH, YOU.
YOU COME OVER HERE...

35:13.111 --> 35:15.184
WHY DID YOU TELL ME THIS NOW?
WHY DO YOU EVEN CARE?

35:15.184 --> 35:18.217
YOU DIDN'T SAY A THING--ALL
THOSE TIMES, ALL THOSE YEARS--

35:18.217 --> 35:20.189
SO WHY NOW?
I DON'T KNOW.

35:20.189 --> 35:23.652
YOU DON'T KNOW?
I DON'T KNOW. I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT DOES IT MATTER TO YOU?

35:23.652 --> 35:27.496
YOU NEVER FELT
THE SAME WAY FOR--
OF COURSE I DID!

35:27.496 --> 35:30.199
OF COURSE I DID.
I HAD ALL THOSE FEELINGS

35:30.199 --> 35:32.331
FOR YOU, TEDDY, FOR YEARS,

35:32.331 --> 35:34.463
BUT YOU NEVER
GAVE ME ANYTHING.
YOU WERE ENGAGED.

35:34.463 --> 35:37.606
YOU NEVER GAVE--FOR YEARS...
YOU WERE ENGAGED.
YOU WERE ENGAGED, YOU IDIOT!

35:37.606 --> 35:40.769
YOU NEVER GAVE ME
ONE DAMN HINT!
YOU IDIOT.

35:40.769 --> 35:44.543
I HAVE LOVED YOU FOREVER.

35:44.543 --> 35:47.846
(voice breaking) I HAVE
LOVED YOU WHEN I WAS COUPLED UP.

35:47.846 --> 35:49.848
I HAVE LOVED YOU
WHEN I WAS SINGLE.

35:49.848 --> 35:53.182
I HAVE LOVED YOU
EVERY SECOND OF EVERY DAY.

35:53.182 --> 35:54.353
TEDDY...

35:54.353 --> 35:57.886
(whispers) I LOVE YOU.
I'M IN LOVE WITH YOU.

35:57.886 --> 36:02.261
♪♪

36:02.261 --> 36:04.533
I'M IN LOVE WITH CRISTINA.

36:15.204 --> 36:19.278
♪♪

36:19.278 --> 36:21.280
(clears throat)
YOU PAGED ME?

36:21.280 --> 36:23.282
UH, I JUST CONFIRMED,
UH, BRAIN DEATH

36:23.282 --> 36:24.783
ON AN 18-YEAR-OLD FEMALE

36:24.783 --> 36:27.386
INVOLVED IN A HEAD-ON M.V.C.
EARLIER THIS EVENING.

36:27.386 --> 36:30.259
SHE'S A MATCH FOR KELSEY.
SO I CALLED U.N.O.S.,

36:30.259 --> 36:32.761
AND THEY GAVE ME THE GO-AHEAD
FOR A DIRECTED DONATION.

36:32.761 --> 36:34.763
NOW DR. BAILEY WILL DO
THE ORGAN RECOVERY,

36:34.763 --> 36:36.765
AND I SET UP O.R. TWO
FOR KELSEY.

36:36.765 --> 36:40.569
THAT IS WHY NEW YEAR'S EVE
IS MY FAVORITE HOLIDAY.
STOP IT.

36:40.569 --> 36:43.272
THIS IS NOT A CELEBRATION.
COME HERE.

36:43.272 --> 36:44.573
(crying) NO.

36:44.573 --> 36:46.775
NO, NO, NO, NOT MY BABY.

36:46.775 --> 36:50.309
PLEASE NOT MY DAUGHTER.
OH, MY... I CAN'T...

36:50.309 --> 36:52.311
THIS IS NOT A CELEBRATION.

36:52.311 --> 36:55.284
NO, NO, NO, YOU CAN'T...

36:55.284 --> 36:57.246
(sobs) OH, NO.

37:04.753 --> 37:07.856
♪♪

37:07.856 --> 37:10.629
YOUR KIDNEY'S
HAVE STABILIZED,

37:10.629 --> 37:13.362
AND YOUR VITALS ARE STABLE,
AND...

37:13.362 --> 37:16.435
EVERYTHING LOOKS GREAT.

37:16.435 --> 37:18.367
FEEL.

37:18.367 --> 37:20.539
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

37:20.539 --> 37:23.011
AWESOME, HUH?

37:23.011 --> 37:25.474
UM, I CAN ONLY REALLY
FEEL YOUR BOOB, SO...
HEY!

37:25.474 --> 37:28.847
YOU WANT TO FEEL?
UH, NO. BUT I WILL LISTEN.

37:28.847 --> 37:32.951
♪♪

37:32.951 --> 37:36.425
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

37:36.425 --> 37:38.727
I KNOW IT'S ONLY BEEN
A COUPLE OF MONTHS.

37:38.727 --> 37:41.430
AND FOUR DATES. IT'S TECHNICALLY
BEEN FOUR DATES.

37:41.430 --> 37:43.962
YOU AMAZE ME... EVERY DAY.

37:43.962 --> 37:45.964
AND WE WENT THROUGH
A WAR TOGETHER.

37:45.964 --> 37:48.967
WE WENT THROUGH THIS TOGETHER,
AND WE CAME OUT THE OTHER SIDE.

37:48.967 --> 37:50.799
AND I THINK...

37:50.799 --> 37:54.343
IF WE CAN GET THROUGH THIS,
WE CAN GET THROUGH ANYTHING.

37:54.343 --> 37:58.046
SO MARRY ME. PLEASE.

37:58.046 --> 37:59.608
YES.

37:59.608 --> 38:01.380
OF COURSE.

38:01.380 --> 38:05.384
♪♪

38:07.856 --> 38:10.859
♪♪

38:26.375 --> 38:29.838
I'M...

38:29.838 --> 38:33.342
INSENSITIVE SOMETIMES.

38:33.342 --> 38:35.344
UM...

38:35.344 --> 38:37.416
BUT I'M NOT OBLIVIOUS.

38:37.416 --> 38:40.419
AND I DON'T WANT YOU TO,
UH, TO BE WITH ME

38:40.419 --> 38:43.392
BECAUSE YOU FEEL LIKE YOU
OWE ME SOMETHING BECAUSE...

38:43.392 --> 38:45.794
I MEAN, YOU TWO
WENT THROUGH WAR TO--

38:45.794 --> 38:48.797
♪♪

38:52.401 --> 38:53.702
I WITH YOU.

38:53.702 --> 38:55.804
I'M WITH YOU
BECAUSE I WANT TO BE.

38:55.804 --> 39:01.339
I'M WITH YOU
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU.

39:01.339 --> 39:03.372
ARE YOU SURE?

39:03.372 --> 39:06.375
♪♪

39:12.681 --> 39:16.685
EVERY DAY, WE GET TO GIVE
THE GIFT OF LIFE.

39:16.685 --> 39:20.859
IT CAN BE PAINFUL,
IT CAN BE TERRIFYING...

39:20.859 --> 39:25.133
BUT IN THE END,
IT'S WORTH IT...

39:25.133 --> 39:27.396
EVERY TIME.

39:27.396 --> 39:31.840
WE ALL HAVE
THE OPPORTUNITY TO GIVE.

39:31.840 --> 39:33.902
MAYBE THE GIFTS
ARE NOT AS DRAMATIC

39:33.902 --> 39:36.475
AS WHAT HAPPENS
IN THE OPERATING ROOM.

39:36.475 --> 39:40.409
UH... SO HOW WAS
NEW YEAR'S EVE AT TUCKER'S?

39:40.409 --> 39:42.150
OH, IT WAS FINE.

39:42.150 --> 39:45.654
I KISSED MY GRANDSON
AT MIDNIGHT EAST COAST TIME,

39:45.654 --> 39:48.386
AND I TUCKED HIM INTO BED.

39:48.386 --> 39:50.619
OKAY. UH, SO YOU'RE
HEADED HOME TODAY?

39:50.619 --> 39:52.621
MOM'S PICKING YOU UP
AT THE AIRPORT?

39:52.621 --> 39:54.392
YEAH.

39:54.392 --> 39:56.124
I, UH...

39:56.124 --> 39:59.397
TUCKED YOU IN EVERY NIGHT
OF YOUR CHILDHOOD.

39:59.397 --> 40:02.901
DAD...
(laughs) I TUCKED YOU IN
AND I KISSED YOU GOODNIGHT

40:02.901 --> 40:06.174
AND I CHECKED UNDER THE BED
FOR BAD GUYS.

40:06.174 --> 40:07.736
(chuckles)

40:07.736 --> 40:12.410
AND YOU WENT AND GREW UP
AND GOT YOURSELF A DIVORCE...

40:12.410 --> 40:15.884
AND DIDN'T BOTHER TO TELL ME.

40:15.884 --> 40:18.487
(Ingrid Michaelson)
♪ ...IN YOUR QUIET LOVE ♪

40:18.487 --> 40:21.690
I-I DIDN'T KNOW HOW
TO... EXPLAIN.

40:21.690 --> 40:24.022
I DIDN'T WANT
TO DISAPPOINT YOU.

40:24.022 --> 40:26.555
I-I DIDN'T WANT TO BE JUDGED.

40:26.555 --> 40:29.427
I'M YOUR FATHER.

40:29.427 --> 40:32.430
CAN YOU IMAGINE IF LITTLE TUCK
GREW UP AND GOT A DIVORCE

40:32.430 --> 40:34.202
AND DIDN'T TELL YOU?

40:34.202 --> 40:37.466
♪ I WANT ♪

40:37.466 --> 40:41.610
♪ A SNOWFALL KIND OF LOVE ♪

40:41.610 --> 40:43.441
THEN I'M SORRY, DAD.

40:43.441 --> 40:45.614
I'M--I'M SO SORRY.

40:45.614 --> 40:49.147
MAYBE THE GIFT IS TO TRY
AND MAKE A SIMPLE APOLOGY.

40:49.147 --> 40:52.681
I'M... NEVER JUDGING YOU.

40:52.681 --> 40:55.053
I'M WORRYING ABOUT YOU.

40:55.053 --> 40:57.155
YOUR MOTHER AND I
WORRY ABOUT YOU.

40:57.155 --> 40:59.027
THAT'S ALL.

40:59.027 --> 41:00.529
♪ OOH ♪

41:00.529 --> 41:02.831
♪ I WANT ♪

41:02.831 --> 41:05.133
♪ A SNOWFALL KIND OF LOVE ♪

41:05.133 --> 41:06.835
LITTLE TUCK,

41:06.835 --> 41:08.997
HE'S A REAL SPITFIRE,
ISN'T HE?

41:08.997 --> 41:10.499
HE IS.

41:10.499 --> 41:12.841
HE SURE IS.

41:12.841 --> 41:17.946
HE DOESN'T SEEM
TOO MUCH WORSE FOR WEAR.

41:17.946 --> 41:20.208
♪ OH, BURY ME... ♪

41:20.208 --> 41:24.082
MAYBE IT'S TO UNDERSTAND
ANOTHER PERSON'S POINT OF VIEW.

41:24.082 --> 41:26.014
♪♪

41:26.014 --> 41:27.986
(bell on door rings)

41:27.986 --> 41:29.618
(indistinct conversations)

41:29.618 --> 41:32.490
HI. I'M SORRY
THAT I PAGED YOU.

41:32.490 --> 41:34.593
HE'S PRETTY PUBLIC HERE,

41:34.593 --> 41:37.596
AND I KNOW WHAT THAT COULD DO,
YOU KNOW, TO HIS CAREER.

41:37.596 --> 41:39.798
I-I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT ELSE TO DO.

41:39.798 --> 41:41.570
(Richard sings indistinctly)

41:41.570 --> 41:45.904
MAYBE IT'S TO HOLD A SECRET
FOR A FRIEND.

41:47.505 --> 41:51.139
♪ I WANT A SNOWFALL... ♪

41:51.139 --> 41:53.642
THE JOY, SUPPOSEDLY,
IS IN THE GIVING.

41:53.642 --> 41:55.584
MEREDITH.

41:55.584 --> 41:58.647
HAPPY NEW YEAR.

41:58.647 --> 42:02.551
SHE IS MY STAR PUPIL, JOE.

42:02.551 --> 42:04.553
MY LITTLE STAR.

42:04.553 --> 42:06.224
AND I'M SO PROUD OF HER.

42:06.224 --> 42:11.199
I AM SO VERY PROUD.

42:11.199 --> 42:15.003
SHE WILL BE
A BRILLIANT SURGEON...

42:15.003 --> 42:16.705
BRILLIANT...

42:16.705 --> 42:19.608
JUST LIKE HER MOTHER.

42:19.608 --> 42:22.170
SO WHEN THE JOY IS GONE...

42:22.170 --> 42:24.973
GET DR. GREY A DRINK, JOE.
TEQUILA.

42:24.973 --> 42:28.076
WHEN THE GIVING STARTS TO FEEL
MORE LIKE A BURDEN...

42:28.076 --> 42:30.018
THAT'S WHEN YOU STOP.

42:30.018 --> 42:34.322
AND, UM... I WILL--
I'LL HAVE ANOTHER CLUB SODA.

42:34.322 --> 42:36.885
BUT IF YOU'RE LIKE
MOST PEOPLE I KNOW...

42:36.885 --> 42:38.887
AND IT'S ON ME--ON ME.

42:38.887 --> 42:42.190
YOU GIVE TILL IT HURTS...

42:42.190 --> 42:47.195
AND THEN YOU GIVE SOME MORE.
